ZH: 我不小心踩死了一只蚂蚁。
EN: I accidentally stepped on and killed an ant.

ZH: 他不小心踩死了一只小鸟。
EN: He accidentally trod on and killed a little bird.

ZH: 让我们一起来踩死这只恶毒的虫子！
EN: Let's step on and squash this vicious bug together!

ZH: 不要踩死草地上的花朵。
EN: Don't trample and crush the flowers on the grass.

ZH: 小猫躺在地上，怕被人踩死。
EN: The kitten lays on the floor, afraid of being stepped on.

ZH: 她把那只臭虫踩死了。
EN: She squashed and killed that stinky bug.

ZH: 走道上的虫子被他踩死了。
EN: The bug on the pathway was squashed by him.

ZH: 我不小心踩死了一只蜜蜂。
EN: I accidentally crushed and killed a bee.

ZH: 他不小心踩死了一只蝴蝶。
EN: He accidentally stepped on and killed a butterfly.

ZH: 小孩踩死了一只小蜗牛。
EN: The child stepped on and killed a small snail.

ZH: 她毫不留情地踩死了那只可怜的老鼠。
EN: She mercilessly stamped on and killed the poor mouse.

ZH: 刚刚踩死的蚊子还在血中。
EN: The mosquito that was just squashed is still in the blood.

ZH: 她意外地踩死了一只小甲虫。
EN: She accidentally crushed and killed a little beetle.

ZH: 那个可怕的昆虫差一点儿把我踩死。
EN: That terrifying insect almost stepped on and killed me.

ZH: 我的狗在草地上踩死了一只蚂蚁。
EN: My dog stepped on and killed an ant on the grass.

ZH: 他眼睛里湿润的泪水差点儿踩死那只小蚕虫。
EN: The tears in his eyes almost stepped on and crushed the little silkworm.

ZH: 怕他踩死了陆龟，孩子赶紧把它放入水中。
EN: Afraid that he would step on and kill the tortoise, the child quickly put it into the water.

ZH: 当我走在草地上时，我总是小心翼翼地避免踩死青蛙。
EN: When I walk on the meadow, I always carefully avoid stepping on and killing the frogs.

ZH: 她坚决不愿来到养蚕场，说怕踩死蚕虫。
EN: She resolutely refused to come to the silkworm farm, saying she was afraid of stepping on and killing the worms.

ZH: 在遛狗时，要小心不要踩死蚂蚁或是其他小动物。
EN: When walking the dog, be careful not to step on and crush ants or other small animals.
